      "question": "For a given frequency distribution, the sum of frequencies $\\sum f_i = 50$ and the sum of the product of frequencies and class marks $\\sum f_i x_i = 1750$. Find the mean of the distribution.",
      "answer": "$35$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Identify the formula for the mean of grouped data, which is $\\bar{x} = \\frac{\\sum f_i x_i}{\\sum f_i}$.",
          "Substitute the given values $\\sum f_i x_i = 1750$ and $\\sum f_i = 50$ into the formula to calculate the mean."
        ],
        "derivation": "$\\bar{x} = \\frac{\\sum f_i x_i}{\\sum f_i} \\\\ \\bar{x} = \\frac{1750}{50} \\\\ \\bar{x} = 35$"
      },
